@startuml
title ECommerce Backend - Data Flow Diagram

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Guest" as Guest
actor "Customer" as Customer
actor "Admin" as Admin
actor "Operations" as Ops

rectangle "ASP.NET Core API\nControllers + Middleware" as API
rectangle "JWT Auth\nClaims + Role Checks" as Auth
rectangle "Application Services\nBusiness Rules" as Services
rectangle "Repositories + UnitOfWork" as Repos
database "SQL Server\nTransactional Store" as SQL
database "Redis / Memory Cache\nCatalog Cache" as Cache
cloud "SMTP Server\nEmail Delivery" as SMTP
cloud "Payment Gateway Simulator" as Gateway
rectangle "Background Workers\nPending Payments + Refund Retries" as Workers
database "Elasticsearch\nStructured Logs" as ES
rectangle "Kibana\nLog Search" as Kibana

Guest --> API : register, login,\nbrowse catalog, read feedback
Customer --> API : cart, address,\norder, payment,\ncancellation, feedback
Admin --> API : catalog management,\norder status,\ncancellation review,\nrefund processing
API --> Auth : validate JWT where required
Auth --> API : customer_id + role claims
API --> Services : DTO requests

Services --> Cache : read product/category by versioned key
Cache --> Services : cache hit
Services --> Repos : cache miss or transactional command
Repos --> SQL : EF Core query/save
SQL --> Repos : entities
Repos --> Services : entities/results
Services --> API : ApiResponse DTOs
API --> Guest : JSON responses
API --> Customer : JSON responses
API --> Admin : JSON responses

Services --> Cache : refresh catalog version on category/product mutation
Services --> Gateway : simulate non-COD payment and refund
Services --> SMTP : send order, cancellation,\nand refund notifications
Workers --> SQL : scan pending payments/refunds every 5 minutes
Workers --> Gateway : retry simulated settlement
Workers --> SMTP : send success notifications

API --> ES : request/action/error logs via Serilog
Services --> ES : service logs via Serilog
Workers --> ES : background job logs via Serilog
Ops --> Kibana : inspect logs
Kibana --> ES : query indices

note bottom of SQL
  Core persisted data:
  customers, addresses, categories, products,
  carts, orders, payments, cancellations,
  refunds, feedback, status seed values.
end note

@enduml
